The paper deals with the problem of achieving strong secrecy over a binary erasure wiretap channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes is a common technique in coding theory (cs.CC) and the paper specifically analyzes ensembles of LDPC codes. The stopping set analysis used in the paper is a technique commonly used in coding theory and information theory, but also has applications in signal processing and communications (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of achieving strong secrecy over a communication channel, which is a topic in networking and network security (cs.NI).
